text: Enus Mariani (born 4 March 1998) is an Italian artistic gymnast."MARIANI Enus". database.fig-gymnastics.com. Retrieved 27 April 2017. ==Senior career== Mariani's first international competition as a senior was the Mexico Open in December 2014; she was fourth in the all-around. At the 2015 City of Jesolo Trophy, Mariani competed on uneven bars in qualifications. At the 2015 World Championships, she helped the Italian team finish seventh. She then competed at the Arthur Gander Memorial in November and placed ninth in the all-around. Mariani finished fifth in the all-around at the 2016 Glasgow World Cup. At the 2016 City of Jesolo Trophy, she won a bronze medal with the Italian team and also placed eleventh in the all-around, sixth on balance beam, and fifth on floor. At the 2016 European Championships, she helped Italy finish fifth in the team competition. ==References== Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Italian female artistic gymnasts Category:People from Cantù
